resources.string: The module\'s activation status directly affects its functionality. If the module isn\'t activated, it won\'t work. The module reports its activation status by hooking its own members. If you suspect a false report, force stop the app and reopen it.

The state of Preferences determines whether the module\'s settings can be saved. Normally, proper usage of LSPosed won\'t cause this state to be abnormal. If the state is abnormal, all module features will be enabled by default.
All changes will take effect immediately
